<p align="center"> 
	<i><b>"HECA is an organization of professionals dedicated to helping students<br>
	and families explore higher education option and opportunities."</b></i>	
</p>
Thank you for your interest in becoming a member of HECA.  <i><u>Membership is for individuals only</u></i>. You may have multiple memberships in an office.  Membership dues are $65.00 payable to HECA,  renewable each year in April.  Be sure to mark on the Membership Application whether you are applying for the <b>"active"</b> level of membership (professionals working directly with students  and families.) or the  <b>"associate"</b> membership (others interested in promoting higher education options and opportunities, such as individuals employed by colleges, youth organizations, and others).  <br>
<br>

<b>Membership in HECA provides:</b><br>
<ol>
	<li>Inclusion in a website directory searchable by name, state, business, and specialties.
	<li>A hardcopy  directory.
	<li>A newsletter addressing the educational and business interests of the members.
	<li>Conferences and seminars that  advance knowledge of members and advance the profession.
	<li>Promotional materials, such as  "Tips for Choosing a Private Counselor" for use in public relations.
	<li>Other services as developed by the organization to support and assist members and the association in fulfilling the mission statement.
</ol>
<b>HECA's Goals for the future include:</b><br>
<ul>
	<li>developing  a membership structure that provides direction and mentoring for consultants new to the profession.
	<li>enhancing and advancing ethical and professional standards within the profession.
	<li>developing collaborative ties with state and national organizations.
	<li>adding services for members,  such as liability insurance and a listserve.
</ul>
